.TH GITIGNORE 1 "January 2026" "gitignore 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gitignore \- professional .gitignore file generator with 17 built-in templates
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gitignore
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR]
[\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR]
[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-init\fR|\fBinit\fR] [\fIlanguages...\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-sync\fR|\fBsync\fR] \fIlanguages...\fR
.br
.B gitignore
[\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-list\fR|\fBlist\fR] [\fIfilter\fR] [\fB\-\-local\fR|\fB\-\-builtin\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fBshow\fR|\fBcat\fR] \fItemplate\fR
.br
.B gitignore
[\fBauto\fR|\fB\-\-auto\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-I\fR|\fBinteractive\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fBappend\fR|\fBupdate\fR] \fIlanguages...\fR
.br
.B gitignore
[\fB\-a\fR|\fB\-\-add\fR] \fIpattern...\fR
.br
.B gitignore
\fIfile_or_pattern...\fR
.br
.B gitignore
\fBglobal\fR [\fBinit\fR|\fBadd\fR \fIlanguages...\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
[\fBbackup\fR|\fBrestore\fR [\fIbackup_name\fR]|\fBbackups\fR|\fBhistory\fR]
.br
.B gitignore
\fBcache clear\fR

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gitignore
is a professional command-line tool with 17 built-in templates compiled into
the binary. It automatically appends to existing .gitignore files, removes
duplicates, and provides smart conflict detection.

.B Key Features:
.br
• 17 built-in templates (no external files needed)
.br
• Smart append mode (preserves existing patterns)
.br
• Automatic duplicate removal
.br
• Multiple pattern support
.br
• Auto-detection of project types
.br
• Interactive mode
.br
• GitHub template sync
.br
• Backup and restore
.br
• Custom template support

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and feature status.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output with detailed operation information.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Quiet mode - only display errors.
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Show what would happen without making any changes.
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-init ", " init " " [\fIlanguages...\fR]
Initialize or update .gitignore file. If .gitignore exists, appends new patterns
and removes duplicates. Uses built-in templates (no external files needed).
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-sync ", " sync " " \fIlanguages...\fR
Download templates from GitHub and merge with existing .gitignore.
Automatically removes duplicates. Requires internet connection.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-list ", " list " " [\fIfilter\fR] [\fB\-\-local\fR|\fB\-\-builtin\fR]
List available templates. Shows 17 built-in templates and any custom templates.
.TP
.BR show ", " cat " " \fItemplate\fR
Display the contents of a template.
.TP
.BR auto ", " \-\-auto
Auto-detect project type and create/update .gitignore accordingly.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-I ", " interactive
Launch interactive mode with a menu to select templates. Quick shortcuts: -t or -I
.TP
.BR append " " \fIlanguages...\fR
Append templates to existing .gitignore. Smart merge with duplicate removal.
.TP
.BR update " " \fIlanguages...\fR
Smart merge templates into existing .gitignore, removing duplicates.
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-add " " \fIpattern...\fR
Force add patterns when name conflicts with commands. Can add multiple patterns at once.
.TP
.BR global " " init
Create a global .gitignore file at ~/.gitignore_global
.TP
.BR global " " add " " \fIlanguages...\fR
Add templates to the global .gitignore file.
.TP
.BR backup
Create a timestamped backup of the current .gitignore file.
.TP
.BR restore " " [\fIbackup_name\fR]
Restore .gitignore from a backup.
.TP
.BR backups ", " history
List all available backup files.
.TP
.BR cache " " clear
Clear the template cache.

.SH ADDING PATTERNS
.B gitignore
can add file patterns directly to .gitignore. Multiple patterns can be added at once.

.TP
.B gitignore \fIpattern...\fR
Add one or more patterns to .gitignore. The tool automatically detects patterns
and removes duplicates.

Examples:
.br
  gitignore node_modules/ *.log .env      # Add 3 patterns at once
.br
  gitignore *.tmp *.swp *~                # Add temp files
.br
  gitignore dist/ build/                  # Add directories

.TP
.B Pattern Detection
Automatically detected as pattern if contains:
.br
• / (slash) - e.g., node_modules/
.br
• * (star) - e.g., *.log
.br
• . (dot) - e.g., .env
.br
• File/directory exists

.TP
.B gitignore \-a \fIpattern\fR
Force add as pattern when name conflicts with commands (init, sync, list, etc.)

Example:
.br
  gitignore --add init sync      # Adds 'init' and 'sync' as patterns

.SH BUILT-IN TEMPLATES
The tool includes 17 templates compiled into the binary:

.B Languages (11):
.br
python, node, rust, c, cpp, java, go, swift, ruby, php, typescript

.B Editors (3):
.br
vscode, vim, intellij

.B Operating Systems (3):
.br
macos, linux, windows

.B Note:
No external template files needed! Templates are compiled at build time.

.SH SMART MERGING
When .gitignore already exists:
.br
• Appends new patterns (does not overwrite)
.br
• Removes duplicate patterns
.br
• Preserves existing patterns
.br
• Works with init, sync, and pattern addition

Example:
.br
.nf
# Existing .gitignore:
node_modules/
.env

# Run: gitignore init python

# Result:
node_modules/     # Kept
.env              # Kept
__pycache__/      # Added
*.py[cod]         # Added
.fi

